## AutoBot
AutoBot is inspired by GitHub's [HUBOT](http://hubot.github.com/) however AutoBot is one for the Windows crew. 
The main Bot is written in C# (.NET 4), his functionality and extensibility is by the addition of PowerShell modules

## Getting AutoBot / Contributing
# Setup Git
http://help.github.com/win-set-up-git/
# To clone the github repo
$ git clone git@github.com:lholman/AutoBot.git

## Hosting AutoBot
http://www.appharbor.com rocks, if everything you want to do is publicly acceessible then you can host AutoBot
at AppHarbor for free.
# To setup and push changes in your repo to AppHarbor
$ git remote add appharbor https://<username>@appharbor.com/<ApplicationName>.git
$ git push appharbor master
#To check build and deployment status
http://appharbor.com/application/<ApplicationName>

## Scripts
AutoBot scripts are written in [PowerShell](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Windows_PowerShell)

